    public interface SQLValue<T>
extends Targetted<T>
    An object that can create a value from a SQL fragment. We encode both the SQL fragment used in the select and the java code needed to convert this to and from a java type in the same class as there is an implicit dependency between the two. Note that though there must be a one-to-one relation between the result of the select and the returned object the makeObject method may apply an arbitrary mapping.
    See Also:
    SQLExpression, GroupingSQLValue, NestedSQLValue
